article_metadata.title: Gov. Rick Scott talks with feds over healthcare funding crisis — and comes up empty | Miami Herald

og.description: “We had a good conversation … but we don’t have a resolution,” Scott said after talking about an hour with Health and Human Services Secretary Sylvia Burwell about renewing a $2.2 billion hospital funding program.
